# General rules for AI

- Always use kebab-case for file names.
- Typesafety and linting are a must in this project.
- Use our internal definition pattern when defining new APIs

## Endpoint definition

- New rest apis must be placed in: `/src/server/api/rest/routers/[feature].ts`
- New trpc apis must be placed in: `/src/server/api/trpc/routers/[feature].ts`
- APIs input must be validated using correct validators
- APIs should use services to keep the code DRY and to follow the SOLID principles

[todos.ts](mdc:src/shared/validators/todo.schema.ts)
[todos.ts](mdc:src/server/api/rest/routers/todos.ts)
[todos.ts](mdc:src/server/api/trpc/routers/todos.ts)

## Service layer

- Always use services to encapsulate business logic
- Services can use queries and mutation from any features
- Queries for a given entity must go into: `/src/server/domain/[feature]/queries.ts`
- Mutations for a given entity must go into: `/src/server/domain/[feature]/mutations.ts`

